com.avaya.csta.binding

Class TransferMonitorObjects

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.TransferMonitorObjects
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TransferMonitorObjects
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is a request to transfer a list of device identifiers from one session identifier to another one. This is intended to be used for client application duplication. For example, to recover a device identifier when the controlling session goes out of service. The TransferMonitorObjects request has these parameters:

    TransferMonitorObjects Request Parameters
    fromSessionID Required Specifies the session from which the devices are transferred. The session must be the current owner of the devices. This session identifier must belong to the same user name that makes the request.
    toSessionID Required Specifies the session to which the devices are transferred. The session will become the new owner of the devices. This session identifier must belong to the user name that makes the request.
    extensions Not used

    The list of transferred device identifiers and their established monitors is returned as a sequence of TransferMonitorObjectsEvent messages following the TransferMonitorObjectsResponse acknowledgement.
